<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-06-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="350" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Riddle</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-06-20"><hi rend="italic">June 20,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 24. Roumanian Series.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith the
                            official text,<note n="a" xml:id="d350fna">Not printed.</note> in French
                            and Roumanian, of a treaty of commerce between Roumania and Russia, in
                            effect April 4, 1906.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. W. Riddle.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>